<p><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino;">The </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Courier;">fmemopen </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino;">function allows the caller to provide a buffer to be used for the memory stream: the </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino; font-style: italic;">buf </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino;">argument points to the beginning of the buffer and the </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino; font-style: italic;">size </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino;">argument specifies the size of the buffer in bytes. If the </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino; font-style: italic;">buf </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino;">argument is null, then the </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Courier;">fmemopen </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino;">function allocates a buffer of </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino; font-style: italic;">size </span><span style=" font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: Palatino;">bytes. In this case, the buffer will be freed when the stream is closed.</span></p>
